  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_electrocardiogram">Electrocardiogram</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_clinical_investigation">Clinical Investigation</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_electrocardiogram">Electrocardiogram</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_electrocardiogram">ECG</xref>
) records the rhythm and electrical activity of the heart.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_electrocardiogram">Electrocardiograms</xref>
, see the NHS website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/coronary-heart-disease/diagnosis/"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Coronary heart disease</xref>
.  </p>

